  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer (2 Years Contract)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Responsible for the management of assigned projects in security systems such as CCTV Surveillance System, Intrusion Detection System, Electronics Access Control System, Audio/Video Intercom System, etc.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for the implementation of installation, testing and commissioning of the security systems as per customer requirements within budget and delivery schedule commitments.</li>\n  <li>Attend site meetings to monitor status of projects.</li>\n  <li>To liaise with Architects, Consultants, Main Contractors, Interior Designers, etc to provide accurate feedback on the progress of works, technical compliance to specifications and variation claims.</li>\n  <li>Procurement of materials and delivery to site in a timely manner in accordance to site progress and within project’s budget.</li>\n  <li>Conduct detailed training to customers on the operational use of the installed, security systems.</li>\n  <li>Ensure subcontractors on-site perform the work in accordance with the approved drawings and instructions as appropriate.</li>\n  <li>Ensure shop drawings, floor plan drawings and single line diagrams are correctly updated for each project before handing over to Maintenance Department.</li>\n  <li>Respond to and manage customer feedback/complaints and take corrective/preventive action.</li>\n  <li>Provide regular updates to relevant stakeholders on progress reports, forecasts, technical problems encountered, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Experiences &amp; Skills</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Electrical and Electronics Engineering, IT Computer Science / networking related or related fields with 2 years of working experience</li>\n  <li>Excellent project and people management skills.</li>\n  <li>Hands-on project execution and management experience.</li>\n  <li>Good oral and written communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Competent in the use of Microsoft Office applications.</li>\n  <li>Good working knowledge on IP data networks</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>",
